column2: "<%me>, how is your quest progressing? I haven't had any luck on my end."
"Forget about finding anyone, I heard that the distress signal has stopped since the report."
"I thought I heard someone's voice, but it must have been something else."
"What?"
"There's... no one there?"
"Where are you looking? Down, hey down!"
"Eeeeeeeh, uuuwhaaa?"
"Hey watch out! What do you think you're doing?"
"The enemy can talk!!?"
"<%me>, get out of the way, we have to take care of this!"
"H-Hey wait! Calm down! Please calm down! I'm not an enemy! R-really I'm not!"
"I'm just a Cabracan who lives here! So just calm down, okay?"
"Just, what are you? You're disgusting!"
"Hey watch it! From where I am, you look a lot worse than I do!"
"You're so slimy, don't get close to me!"
"Don't make fun of other people's differences! You could stand to learn a lot from me!"
"While looking for someone I can't believe we have to put up with something as rude as this!"
"Looking for someone?"
"Have you seen someone else that looks just like me?"
"This is definitely my first time seeing anything as revolting as you."
"Don't say revolting!"
"Fine, I have nothing to say to you anymore. Smell you later."
"This native creature, we haven't come in contact with them before, so how can they understand our words?"
